args: ▷You're going to sneak into an\nEx Machina base, Eirene?!◁
It won't be a problem. I've already run\nsimulations on my infiltration strategy.
If I eliminate variables, I project a 90\npercent success rate. The risk is\nsufficiently low to justify the attempt.
▷Let's go too, Laxi. Should worse\ncome to worst, it'd be prudent to\nhave more firepower on our side.◁
No. I'm going alone. Forgive me, but you\nall are exactly the sort of variables I want\nto eliminate.
There are some things that only\nEx Machina androids can do.
I'll commence laying the groundwork for\nmy plan. My target is...
Seems as though many of them have\nbeen abandoned in the city outskirts.\nNow to check their condition.
These are too badly damaged to be\nof any use. On to the next.
Hm... These are in even worse shape.
So few of these androids are fully intact.\nI suspect those that retain ambulatory\nfunctions have already returned to base.
Still, I only need one for the plan to work.
...! Yes, this one will do.\nDamage is within permissible limits!
Forgive me. I have to borrow some\nof your exterior components.
Mission phase one: complete.\nNow to bring these parts with me...
I've arrived near the base.\nCommencing phase two.
I'll detach my reinforced armor and\nreplace it with the parts I picked up...
Component integration check: clear.\nAll systems green.
But for this plan to work, ＂no problem＂\nmeans there actually IS a problem!\nAnd so...
Ngh... Condition yellow.\nDamage to arms and legs confirmed.
Now the pieces are all in place.\nCommencing infiltration!
(...Maintenance complete. All is\nproceeding in line with my projections.)
(Now for the final phase. My target\nis the database in the maintenance area.)
(All the information needed to\nperform maintenance work is there.)
(Opening connection! Show me\nthe blueprints for me and Finni!)
